# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# PaperTrader frontend — environment variables (EXAMPLE)
#
# Copy this file to `.env` (or `.env.local`) and fill in real values.
# `.env*` files are gitignored — never commit real secrets.
#
# RULES (see CLAUDE.md / ARCHITECTURE.md at the repo root):
#   • Anything prefixed VITE_ is PUBLIC — it ships to the browser.
#     Only put non-secret, publishable values here (public URLs,
#     publishable/anon keys, analytics IDs).
#   • NEVER put the market-data API key (Finnhub / Twelve Data) or any
#     server secret in a VITE_ var. Those live ONLY in Supabase secrets
#     and are used from Edge Functions — never the frontend.
#   • Server-only values (no VITE_ prefix) are read in *.server.ts files
#     or createServerFn handlers and are not bundled to the client.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Supabase (Phase 3+) ───────────────────────────────────────
# Both values are PUBLIC and safe for the browser. Find them in the
# Supabase dashboard → Project Settings → API.

# Supabase project URL.
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-ref.supabase.co

# Supabase publishable / anon key (browser-safe public key).
# New projects show a key prefixed `sb_publishable_...`; older ones an
# `anon` JWT. Either works here — both are public, never a secret.
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=sb_publishable_your_publishable_key
